{"id":"prob-exp-001","subject":"Probability","topic":"Expectation & Variance","subtopic":"Variance of Linear Combinations","difficulty":"intermediate","question":"X,Y independent with Var(X)=4, Var(Y)=9. What is Var(2X-3Y)?","options":{"A":"97","B":"43","C":"25","D":"65"},"answer":"A","explanation":"Var(2X-3Y) = 4·Var(X)+9·Var(Y) = 16+81 = 97."}
